        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 7:57AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 757 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles northeast of Northwest Arkansas Regional
Airport to 2 miles west of Blackburn. Movement was northeast at 55
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Walnut Grove...                   Garfield...
Rogers...                         Woolsey...
Northwest Arkansas Regional Air...Elkins...
West Fork...                      Tontitown...
Larue...                          Pea Ridge...
Cave Springs...                   Bentonville...
Avoca...                          Gateway...
Centerton...                      Rocky Comfort...
Wheeler...                        Sonora...
Springdale...                     Prairie Grove Battlefield State...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 47 and 91.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
